Phase 1: Infrastructure & Database — COMPLETE

Completed at: 2026-03-18

## What was done

### 1. Drizzle Schema (22 tables)
Created `db/schema/` directory with modular schema files:
- `enums.ts` — 12 PostgreSQL enums (user_role, team, lead_status, case_status, task_status, etc.)
- `organizations.ts` — Multi-tenant organization table
- `users.ts` — Users with role, team, and auth_user_id (links to Supabase Auth)
- `leads.ts` — Lead pipeline with intake data
- `cases.ts` — Core cases table with SSA-specific fields, stage groups, stages, assignments, transitions
- `contacts.ts` — Contacts and case-contact junction table
- `custom-fields.ts` — Field definitions (team-segmented) and field values (EAV pattern)
- `workflows.ts` — Workflow templates and task templates (stage-triggered automation)
- `tasks.ts` — Tasks with workflow source tracking
- `documents.ts` — Documents, templates, and signature requests
- `communications.ts` — Inbound/outbound messages and emails
- `calendar.ts` — Calendar events with hearing-specific fields and attendees
- `audit.ts` — Audit log for all entity changes
- `index.ts` — Barrel export

### 2. Drizzle DB Client
- `db/drizzle.ts` — Drizzle ORM client instance using postgres.js

### 3. Migrations
- `supabase/migrations/0000_panoramic_wraith.sql` — Schema creation migration
- `supabase/migrations/0001_rls_policies.sql` — RLS policies

### 4. RLS Policies (48 policies)
- All 22 tables have RLS enabled
- Helper functions: `public.user_org_id()`, `public.app_user_id()`, `public.user_role()`
- Organization-scoped access on all org-owned tables
- Join-based scoping for junction tables (case_assignments, case_contacts, etc.)
- Admin-only write access for config tables (stages, workflows, field definitions, templates)
- Read access for all authenticated users within their org

### 5. Supabase Utilities (pre-existing, verified)
- `db/client.ts` — Browser Supabase client
- `db/server.ts` — Server Supabase client
- `db/middleware.ts` — Auth session refresh middleware

### 6. Schema pushed to staging database
- All tables and RLS policies are live on staging Supabase
